{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"4331","heading":"Regulations","label":"4331 Regulations","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s4331","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/ptIII/ch43/schIV","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs4331","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Prior ProvisionsA prior section 4331 was renumbered .section 7631 of this title","Amendments2006—Subsec. (b)(2)(C). substituted “section 2302(a)(2)(C)(ii)” for “section 2303(a)(2)(C)(ii)”.Pub. L. 109–233","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Effective DateSection effective with respect to reemployments initiated on or after the first day after the 60-day period beginning , with transition rules, see , set out as a note under .Oct. 13, 1994section 8 of Pub. L. 103–353section 4301 of this title"],"amendments":["Amendments2006—Subsec. (b)(2)(C). substituted “section 2302(a)(2)(C)(ii)” for “section 2303(a)(2)(C)(ii)”.Pub. L. 109–233"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":null,"label":"a","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s4331/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s4331","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs4331%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary (in consultation with the Secretary of Defense) may prescribe regulations implementing the provisions of this chapter with regard to the application of this chapter to States, local governments, and private employers.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":null,"label":"b","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s4331/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s4331","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs4331%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s4331/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s4331/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs4331%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Director of the Office of Personnel Management (in consultation with the Secretary and the Secretary of Defense) may prescribe regulations implementing the provisions of this chapter with regard to the application of this chapter to Federal executive agencies (other than the agencies referred to in paragraph (2)) as employers. Such regulations shall be consistent with the regulations pertaining to the States as employers and private employers, except that employees of the Federal Government may be given greater or additional rights.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s4331/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s4331/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs4331%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s4331/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s4331/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs4331%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Merit Systems Protection Board.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s4331/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s4331/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs4331%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Office of Special Counsel.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s4331/b/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s4331/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs4331%2Fb%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The agencies referred to in .section 2302(a)(2)(C)(ii) of title 5","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]}
